[size=3][b]GitHub: [url=https://github.com/damiansirbu-stalker/TestZone]https://github.com/damiansirbu-stalker/TestZone[/url][/b][/size]
[size=3][b]Changelog: [url=https://github.com/damiansirbu-stalker/TestZone/blob/main/doc/changelog]doc/changelog[/url][/b][/size]

[line]

[size=3][b]Features[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][b]Watcher[/b] - monitors all 162 engine callbacks with fire counts and payload logging
[*][b]Deep introspection[/b] - extracts detailed info from tables and userdata arguments
[*][b]Rate limiting[/b] - prevents log spam from high-frequency callbacks
[*][b]Per-callback toggles[/b] - enable/disable individual callbacks via MCM
[*][b]Periodic statistics[/b] - logs top-firing callbacks at configurable intervals
[/list]

[line]

[size=3][b]Requirements[/b][/size]
[list]
[*]Anomaly 1.5.3
[*]Modded exes
[*][url=https://www.moddb.com/mods/stalker-anomaly/addons/xlibs-1001]xlibs[/url]
[*]MCM
[/list]

[line]

[size=3][b]Install (MO2)[/b][/size]
[list]
[*]1. Install xlibs (load first)
[*]2. Install TestZone
[*]3. Load order does not matter
[*]4. Configure via MCM (Options -> TestZone)
[/list]

[line]

[size=3][b]Uninstall (MO2)[/b][/size]
Disable or remove in MO2.

[line]

[size=3][b]Configuration[/b][/size]

[size=2][b]Main tab:[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][b]Watcher enabled[/b] - master toggle for callback logging
[*][b]Periodic statistics[/b] - log callback fire counts at regular intervals
[*][b]Stats interval[/b] - how often to log periodic stats (10-3600 seconds)
[*][b]Log payload[/b] - log callback arguments (can create large log files)
[*][b]Deep introspection[/b] - extract detailed info from objects
[*][b]Table depth[/b] - recursion depth for table introspection (1-4)
[*][b]Rate limiting[/b] - throttle repeated callback logs
[*][b]Rate limit interval[/b] - min ms between same callback logs (100-10000)
[/list]

[size=2][b]Tracked Events tab:[/b][/size]
[list]
[*]Per-callback enable/disable toggles for all 162 callbacks
[/list]

Log output: appdata/logs/testzone.log

[line]

[size=3][b]Compatibility[/b][/size]
No known incompatibilities.

[line]

[size=3][b]Credits[/b][/size]
DrakoMT and SaloEater for their support.
Demonized, Catspaw, Vintar0, RavenAscendant, xcvb, lizzardman, Aoldri, and Feel_Fried. Their work on the engine, modded exes, scripts, and tools shaped how Anomaly modding is done.

[line]

[size=3][b]Development[/b][/size]
Written against X-Ray Monolith engine source, Demonized exes source code, and Anomaly 1.5.3 unpacked gamedata.
Code patterns and engine usage validated against established work by reputable GAMMA modders (Demonized, Vintar0, RavenAscendant, xcvb).
The code is validated in real time by a multi-stage pipeline: luacheck, selene, tree-sitter AST analysis, contract rules, cross-file dependency resolution, cyclomatic complexity analysis, crash and vulnerability pattern detection, lua54 integration testing with X-Ray engine stubs, gitleaks secret scanning.
Full report in doc/test-report.log.

[line]

[size=3][b]Usage and License[/b][/size]
[list]
[*]Modpacks: allowed and encouraged. Keep the readme and license files.
[*]Addons, patches, integrations: allowed. Credit "TestZone by Damian Sirbu" visibly on your mod page.
[*]Full license in LICENSE file and on GitHub.
[/list]

